        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 8:07PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 807 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Macomb Township to near Sterling Heights
to near Troy. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Warren, St. Clair Shores, Mount Clemens, New Baltimore, Richmond, St.
Clair, Algonac, Sterling Heights, Rochester, Marine City, Clinton,
Harsens Island, Macomb Township, Roseville, Eastpointe, Grosse Pointe
Woods, Fraser, Harper Woods, Center Line, and Utica.

People attending Sterlingfest , and Jimmy Johns Field  should seek
safe shelter immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
southeastern Michigan.</instruction>
